<title>USA: Forte plunges on cost outlook, downgrade.</title>
<headline>Forte plunges on cost outlook, downgrade.</headline>
<dateline>PALO ALTO, Calif. 1997-04-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Forte Software Inc's stock lost half its value Friday after executives cautioned investors that the software company will spend more on sales in coming quarters, hurting the earnings outlook.</p>
<p>&quot;Spending will be up next year in sales and marketing,&quot; said Jim Pickrel, analyst at Hambrecht &amp; Quist, who heard the call Thursday. &quot;A lot earnings estimates went down.&quot;</p>
<p>Forte plunged 7-7/8 to 8-3/4 on Nasdaq trading of 4.1 million shares, making the stock the fourth most-active in U.S. markets. The stock was also one of the biggest decliners.</p>
